rest_of_day_open: I see it going well. I plan on doing some reading, some minor house fixes, cooking, and exercise. I look forward to the week, but there is nothing special about it. I may begin planning a winter road trip if I have the time, but definitely not rushing any planning.
critical_positive: We had some things in common. She was going into a business related field and I studied business when I was in college. She asked a decent amount of questions when there were pauses. I tried to do the same when possible. Audio and video quality was good on both sides.
critical_negative: Obviously there are two people involved in any conversation, but I had great difficulty getting any depth out of her. Her answers were very one dimensional and hard to find flow. A lot of the conversation felt forced on both ends, almost like an interview. I don't think either of us had a very good experience.

rest_of_day_open: I'm a little nervous, to be honest. I have a lot of work to do, both in class and with my part-time job. I honestly see myself being totally burn out this week. I'm also having a rough patch with my boyfriend so that only adds to my stress this week.
critical_positive: I think we both had similar backgrounds or aspirations in terms of business and career so we were able to relate over that and share some stories. We also were both generally low-key, not aggressive people so there wasn't too much high energy or someone talking over one another. We got along well.
critical_negative: There were certainly some awkward pauses and gaps in the conversation because the career stuff was basically our main connection. After that, it was hard to find a lot of common ground since we came from different places and generations. It wasn't too bad but there was some fumbling for a next question.
